Privacy Policy

Welcome to Tap In, operated by Jeffjitsu, LLC. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, store, and protect your personal information in compliance with the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA).

Information Collection and Use: We collect and store data necessary for providing our services effectively. This includes personal details you provide directly to us, such as your name, email address, and user preferences. All data is stored securely on Firebase servers, adhering to stringent security measures.

Data Access and Control: You have the right to access, correct, delete, and restrict the use of your personal information held by us. Should you wish to exercise these rights or have any concerns about your privacy, please contact us at jeffjitsu.llc@gmail.com.

Data Protection and Security: Your data is protected using industry-standard security protocols and practices implemented through Firebase. We take all reasonable precautions to safeguard your information against unauthorized access, disclosure, or misuse.

Data Usage and Sharing: We do not sell your personal information to third parties. Data collected is solely used to enhance your experience within our app and improve our services. We may share anonymized data for analytical purposes, but your identifiable information remains private and secure.

Policy Updates: We may update this Privacy Policy periodically to reflect changes in our practices or legal requirements. Any updates will be communicated to you through the app or via email.

Contact Us: For questions or inquiries regarding this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please contact Jeffjitsu, LLC at jeffjitsu.llc@gmail.com.
